{
  "doc_id": "46666",
  "text": "Conclusions. Some orange cheese coryneform bacteria produce antibacterial substances such as bacteriocins, but to date only two, linencin A and linocin M18, have been purified and identified [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Linencin A, a 95-kDa protein, was active only against strains of B. linens [CITATION_4] , whereas linocin M18 which consists of a 31-kDa protein was active against several gram-positive bacteria [CITATION_5] .",
